// Session Lessons Tools
// Records and retrieves lessons learned during collab sessions.
// Lessons are appended to LESSONS.md inside the session's documents folder.

Lessons are stored as markdown sections: ## {timestamp} [{category}]\n{content}.
Categories: universal, codebase, workflow, gotcha. Default is universal.

FUNCTION getLessonsPath(project, session) -> string
  Returns the path to LESSONS.md for the session.

---

FUNCTION fileExists(path) -> boolean
  Returns true if the file is accessible, false otherwise.

---

FUNCTION formatTimestamp() -> string
  Returns the current time as a "YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS" string.

---

FUNCTION addLesson(project, session, lesson, category?) -> AddLessonResult       EXPORT
  Ensure the documents directory exists.
  IF LESSONS.md does not exist, create it with a standard header.
  Append a new section formatted as "## {timestamp} [{category}]\n{lesson}".
  Count existing lessons by matching timestamp headers. Return { success, lessonCount, message }.

---

FUNCTION listLessons(project, session) -> ListLessonsResult                       EXPORT
  IF LESSONS.md does not exist, return empty list.
  Parse each lesson section (timestamp, category, content) using a regex pattern.
  Return { lessons: [...], count }.
